abstract: Thousands of people have fled to the Turkish border from the last big opposition stronghold in northwestern Syria because of an intensified bombardment by Russian forces and the Syrian army, residents and rescue workers said on Friday.
snippet: Thousands of people have fled to the Turkish border from the last big opposition stronghold in northwestern Syria because of an intensified bombardment by Russian forces and the Syrian army, residents and rescue workers said on Friday.
lead_paragraph: BEIRUT — Thousands of people have fled to the Turkish border from the last big opposition stronghold in northwestern Syria because of an intensified bombardment by Russian forces and the Syrian army, residents and rescue workers said on Friday.
headline_main: Thousands Flee Bombardment in Northwest Syria, Head to Turkish Border
headline_print_headline: Thousands Flee Bombardment in Northwest Syria, Head to Turkish Border

abstract: U.S. presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg has spent more on campaign ads in the last few weeks than his main Democratic rivals have all year. Yet his level of support has barely risen, according to a Reuters/Ipsos poll.
snippet: U.S. presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg has spent more on campaign ads in the last few weeks than his main Democratic rivals have all year. Yet his level of support has barely risen, according to a Reuters/Ipsos poll.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON/NEW YORK — U.S. presidential candidate Michael Bloomberg has spent more on campaign ads in the last few weeks than his main Democratic rivals have all year. Yet his level of support has barely risen, according to a Reuters/Ipsos poll.
headline_main: What Does Millions in Ad Spending Get You? So Far for Bloomberg, a Few Points
headline_print_headline: What Does Millions in Ad Spending Get You? So Far for Bloomberg, a Few Points

abstract: Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe on Friday briefed Iranian President Hassan Rouhani on Tokyo's plan to send naval forces  to the Middle East to protect Japanese vessels, a Japanese official said.
snippet: Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe on Friday briefed Iranian President Hassan Rouhani on Tokyo's plan to send naval forces  to the Middle East to protect Japanese vessels, a Japanese official said.
lead_paragraph: TOKYO — Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe on Friday briefed Iranian President Hassan Rouhani on Tokyo's plan to send naval forces to the Middle East to protect Japanese vessels, a Japanese official said.
headline_main: Japan Briefs Iran on Plan to Send Forces to Middle East
headline_print_headline: Japan Briefs Iran on Plan to Send Forces to Middle East

abstract: The director’s inspirations soar beyond Louisa May Alcott’s novel.
snippet: The director’s inspirations soar beyond Louisa May Alcott’s novel.
lead_paragraph: The novel was just the beginning. Greta Gerwig’s adaptation of Louisa May Alcott’s “Little Women” is so teeming with references — literary, artistic, cinematic — that it cries out for a syllabus. “Every line and every moment in this movie could be footnoted,” Gerwig said. “I hope this doesn’t make it sound utterly dull, but it’s a thesis.”

abstract: European parties to the Iran nuclear deal are likely to trigger a dispute resolution process in January to force Tehran to rollback violations, but would stop short of rushing to restore U.N. sanctions that would kill off the accord, diplomats said.
